### AidFlow API — Vendors endpoints
# REST Client extension: click 'Send Request' above each block

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@token = REPLACE_WITH_JWT_TOKEN

### List vendors (501 in Sprint 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/vendors
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get vendor by ID (501 in Sprint 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/vendors/VENDOR_ID
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Register vendor (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/vendors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Acme Supplies Ltd",
  "contactEmail": "contact@acme.example",
  "phone": "+254700000000",
  "location": "Nairobi, Kenya",
  "category": "food"
}

### Update vendor (501 in Sprint 1)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/vendors/VENDOR_ID
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "category": "medical"
}

### Approve vendor (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/vendors/VENDOR_ID/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
